 Ondo State Governor Oluwarotimi Akeredolu has mourned his Chief of Protocol (CoP), Tosin Ogunbodede, who died last Saturday. This is happening a few weeks after the death of the Commissioner for Regional Integration and Special Duties, Prof. Bayonle Ademodi. Ogunbodede died in an accident while returning from Ibadan, the Oyo State capital. He and his driver died when their Toyota Corola car rammed into a trailer on Ilesa-Akure road. Ogunbodede’s remains will arrive Owo, his hometown, today for the beginning of preparations for his funeral. Information and Orientation Commissioner Donald Ojogo, in a statement, said the deceased performed his duties well He described Ogunbodede as a loyal aide of the governor. The statement said: “For Governor Akeredolu, this is a personal loss. It becomes more emotional when it is recalled that the loyal and dedicated Tosin stopped by at the Governor’s Law Hub in Ibadan to greet his principal while returning to Akure from his uncle’s home. “Even with a heavy heart, Governor Akeredolu enjoins all to take solace in the fact of God’s infallibility-He Giveth and Taketh. This is just as he expresses the heartfelt condolence of his immediate family, government and the good people of Ondo State to the wife, children and the family of his late CoP. “The government shall unveil burial plans after consultations with the bereaved family.” Last July, Health Commissioner Dr. Wahab Adegbenro died of COVID-19 complications.